INSERT INTO quarterbacks VALUES('44','Jameis Winston','Saints','QB','26.0','42.0','327.0','2.0','2.0','2.0','11.0','0.0','Winston signed with the Saints following five tumultuous seasons in Tampa Bay. The 2015 first overall pick''s 2019 season was the definition of ''YOLO,'' as he led the NFL in passing yards (5,109), was second in passing touchdowns (33) and finished sixth in YPA (8.2) -- but he also completed an ugly 60.7% of his passes and threw an astounding 30 interceptions (the most the league has seen in a single season since 1988). At best, Winston will be the No. 2 QB behind Drew Brees this season, though he''s not even assured starting duties in the event of a Brees injury with Taysom Hill also in the fold. Do not draft Winston.');
