INSERT INTO quarterbacks VALUES('60','Jordan Love','Packers','QB','16.0','27.0','183.0','1.0','1.0','1.0','5.0','0.0','The Packers traded up to select Love with the 26th pick of April''s draft. Love was very impressive at Utah State back in 2018 but struggled a bit last season. Love tossed 20 touchdowns and 17 interceptions, was off target on a class-high 15.5% of his throws, and his 51.7 total QBR was worst in the class. Love has a good arm, which shows up in his big plays, but his struggles with accuracy, turnovers and decision-making and against pressure stick out as red flags. There''s obvious upside here, but Love is one of the league''s youngest quarterbacks and will require some polish. He''ll have time to work at it with Rodgers positioned as Green Bay''s starter for the next season or three. Love obviously does not need to be drafted in 2020 leagues.');
