INSERT INTO running_backs VALUES('122','DeeJay Dallas','Seahawks','RB','0.0','0.0','0.0','4.0','39.0','0.0','The Seahawks selected Dallas in the fourth round of April''s draft. The Miami product stands 5-foot-10, 217 pounds with an excellent combination of power, burst and elusiveness. He posted terrific rushing efficiency last season, ranking fifth in the 2020 rookie class in YAC (3.7) and seventh in PFF''s forced missed tackle rate (3.8). Dallas is inexperienced as a receiver (33 career targets), though he averaged an outstanding 9.6 yards per target on those plays. He''ll open his career behind Chris Carson, but could be as high as second on the depth chart if Rashaad Penny isn''t ready to go. Monitor Dallas'' progress this summer.');
