INSERT INTO wide_receivers VALUES('179','Isaiah Hodgins','Bills','WR','3.0','35.0','0.0','0.0','0.0','0.0','Buffalo drafted Hodgins in the sixth round of April''s draft. The Oregon State product is a huge receiver with a 6-foot-4, 210-pound frame and 80.5-inch wingspan. His ball skills are outstanding, and he also has great hands (one drop on 123 targets in 2019) and contested catch ability. A lack of speed (4.61 40-yard dash) and strength (nine bench reps) are concerns, though he showed off his quickness with a wideout-best 4.12 short shuttle at the combine. Hodgins is a deep dynasty league stash with little 2020 fantasy appeal.');
