INSERT INTO tight_ends VALUES('81','Harrison Bryant','Browns','TE','6.0','71.0','1.0','0.0','0.0','0.0','The Browns selected Bryant in the fourth round of April''s draft. Bryant''s numbers were off the charts at Florida Atlantic last season, as he averaged a class-best 3.1 yards per route run while posting a 65-1,004-7 receiving line on 99 targets. Bryant is a terrific receiver, and that figures to be his primary focus in the pros, but he''s not a zero as a blocker, which could lead to the coveted every-down role. Bryant''s hands are a slight concern, and he didn''t show well athletically at the combine, but his receiving prowess makes him an intriguing prospect. He won''t be fantasy relevant for a long time with Austin Hooper and David Njoku ahead of him in Cleveland.');
